Sentencas: Important advances have been made in SOFC development utilizing a ceramic framework based upon yttria zirconia (YSZ) electrolytes supported upon porous YSZ electrode skeletons.
Titulo: Development and Performance of MnFeCrO4-Based Electrodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This ceramic framework is sintered at high temperatures with subsequent impregnation and low temperature processing of the active electrode materials.
Titulo: Development and Performance of MnFeCrO4-Based Electrodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Here we seek to develop this impregnated electrode concept by investigating a novel scaffold material similar to the main corrosion product of ferritic stainless steel.
Titulo: Development and Performance of MnFeCrO4-Based Electrodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The chromium rich spinel (MnFeCrO4) was used as an electrode support material, either alone or impregnated with (La0.75Sr0.25)(0.97)Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-delta,La0.8Sr0.2FeO3-delta, Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-delta, CeO2 and/or Pd.
Titulo: Development and Performance of MnFeCrO4-Based Electrodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In these initial studies it was found that all of the impregnated phases adhere very well to the spinel and considerably enhance performance and stability to a level sufficient for SOFC applications.
Titulo: Development and Performance of MnFeCrO4-Based Electrodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
